    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''How the Studios Used Children to Test-Market Violent Films,'' (front page, Sept. 27):</p>
        <p>So now we know: Hollywood would market slasher films to toddlers if there was a buck to be made. Hey, I'm shocked.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''How the Studios Used Children to Test-Market Violent Films,'' (front page, Sept. 27):</p>
        <p>So now we know: Hollywood would market slasher films to toddlers if there was a buck to be made. Hey, I'm shocked.</p>
        <p>Here's a question: Where are the parents of the 10-year-olds who were  recruited to be in focus groups for R-rated movies? Unless these children are being snatched off the street in broad daylight, someone is giving permission for them to be used in this fashion by the movie studios.</p>
        <p>It's getting to be a sad refrain, isn't it: Where are the parents?</p>
        <p>JULIE KIMBALL  Vineyard Haven, Mass.  Sept. 29, 2000</p>
      </block>
